The article highlights the positive impact of President Trump's tax cuts on small businesses and job-seekers in the United States. It mentions that at least two million Americans will receive tax reform bonuses, and Americans' optimism about the job market reached a record high in 2017. The National Federation of Independent Businesses reported that small-business confidence also hit a record high in 2017. Economists credit Trump's policies, including the tax cuts, for positive effects on economic growth, hiring, and the stock market. The article also mentions that utility companies are planning to cut rates as a result of the tax reform. Overall, the article portrays a sense of optimism and confidence in the US economy due to the President's tax cuts.